cs.NI, cs.SD, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the development, deployment, and maintenance of virtualized network services, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE). It also discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) and network function virtualization (NFV), which are related to software development (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper introduces a Software Development Kit (SDK), which is a tool for software development (cs.SE) and could potentially be used in software-defined systems (cs.SD).
